<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1319,1532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,335,1319,1345]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Identification:</emphasis>
Forewing length 9.0–10.5 mm. 
<taxonomicName box="[727,997,1320,1345]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ponometia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candefacta">
<emphasis box="[727,997,1320,1345]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Ponometia candefacta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a white forewing with a brown, fused medial and postmedial lines, and a prominent round, gray reniform spot that is outlined in white. There can be some faint yellow scales proximal to the reniform spot between the brown costal spot and brown band. The orbicular spot is a tiny black dot. The prominent reniform spot distinguishes it from 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenee" authorityName="Guenee" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ponometia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erastrioides">
<emphasis box="[1258,1436,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">P. erastrioides</emphasis>
(Guenée)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[287,573,1469,1494]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ponometia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candefacta">
<emphasis box="[287,573,1469,1494]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Ponometia candefacta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenee" authorityName="Guenee" box="[638,952,1469,1495]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ponometia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erastrioides">
<emphasis box="[638,825,1469,1494]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">P. erastrioides</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[834,844,1469,1495]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">(</emphasis>
Guenée
<emphasis bold="true" box="[941,952,1469,1495]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are considered to be congeneric with 
<taxonomicName authority="Herrich-Schaffer 1868 (Poole and Lafontaine 2010)" authorityName="Herrich-Schaffer 1868 (Poole and Lafontaine" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,895,1506,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ponometia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,278,1507,1532]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Ponometia</emphasis>
Herrich-Schäffer 
<number box="[490,549,1506,1532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1868.0">1868</number>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Poole" box="[564,888,1506,1532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="16" refString="Lafontaine, J. D. &amp; Poole, R. W. (2010) Review of the New World genera of the Subfamily Acontiinae (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae). ZooKeys, 39, 137 - 160." type="journal article" year="2010">
Poole and Lafontaine 
<number box="[824,888,1506,1532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
